first
welcome to servlet

start 
contains different examples about
annotation(/annotation), count view on the website(/count), mime file download(/mime), load pictures(/picture), display time(/time)

login
jdbc+servlet && using servletcontext and context parameter

session1
to get session information and to example of HttpSession

cookies
Session tracking method using cookies-how to create a new cookie, addcookie(cookie), getcookie()

url
type of session tracking .basic example of getParameter(), getWriter() (/books.html)

session
session tracking method-http session with url rewriting and cookies

hff
session tracking method- hidden form fields

scl
type of servlet listener-servletcontextlistener, getServletContext(), setAttribute(), getAttribute()

hsl
type of servlet listener-httpsessionlistener, getsession()

filters1
basic example of filter and connectivity of database (login and welcome page)

filters
example of getServletContext. how many times a web page is executed

redirect(search bar-redirecting to google)
example of sendRedirect(), this method is used to redirect response to another resource

redirect1(servlet+jsp)(login and welcome page)
RequestDispatcher interface, consists of 2 methods-forward("/servlet")&include("/servlet")  

jsp
contains various examples of how to use jsp tags and how to use jsp tags in html. time, count, table, login page(DB connectivity) etc 

bean
jsp with java beans(jsp+java). useBean, setProperty, getProperty simple example.(welcome message)

bean2
jsp with java bean(jsp+html+java). example of multiple getter and setter methods.
